**Clarifying React behavior**

I’m exploring how React handles state. I think if the state remains the same, there shouldn't be a re-render. That means if the effect sets the same state, it won't trigger a rendering cycle. This makes sense because React optimizes performance by not unnecessarily re-rendering components when their state hasn't changed. It's interesting how this optimization works, as it can really help with the speed and efficiency of applications!
